    {
      "para_id": "Q001456.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(1) Whoever erases the inscription of Utu-heĝal , the powerful man , king of Unug , king of the four quarters , and writes his own name there — or make someone else do it on account of this curse — , or destroys this ( bowl ) , may his reign be cut short , may his lineage come to an end ! May An , the king of the gods , and Inana , lady of Unug , curse his ...!"
    }
  ],
